DTEND:20260511T180000Z
SUMMARY:Takeaways From The First International Conference On Transitioning 
 Away From Fossil Fuels
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Environmental Justice'\, 'Lang Center for Civic
  & Social Responsil']\\nCategory: Student Activity (no alcohol)\\nLang Opp
 ortunity Scholar Keanu Arpels-Josiah '28\, a longtime climate justice orga
 nizer and environmental studies student\, will reflect on his recent retur
 n from The First International Conference on Transitioning Away From Fossi
 l Fuels.  The conference was hosted in April in Santa Marta\, Colombia\, a
 s a space for committed governments\, civil society\, youth\, and indigeno
 us leaders to come together and chart a future beyond fossil fuels. The cl
 ear thread was the implication of the broader systems of imperialism\, pat
 riarchy\, and extractivism\, whose end is necessary for such a transition 
 to be possible — and whose biggest enforcer remains to be the United Sta
 tes. The talk is entitled How We Dismantle The Petromasculine-Tech-Imperi
 al Industrial Complex: Takeaways From The First International Conference O
 n Transitioning Away From Fossil Fuels\, and it is sponsored by the Enviro
 nmental Justice & Community Resilience Program at the Lang Center.\\nDetai
 ls: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid
 %3D1395827513
LOCATION:Intercultural Center Big Room - ICC
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1395827513
CATEGORIES:Student Activity (no alcohol)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7d4dfa06af336447@swarthmore-dash-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260508T121334Z
DTSTART:20260512T000000Z
DTEND:20260512T010000Z
SUMMARY:Swat Talk: Laura Hirai `22
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['College Advancement']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel
  Discussion\\nIn a League of Her Own:A Conversation with Women’s Basebal
 l Pioneer Laura Hirai ’22 Please join Laura for a conversation with Ana 
 Apostoleris Rivera ’13 about her pioneering experiences and her insights
  on the future of women's baseball. RSVP here As a young girl\, Laura Hira
 i ’22 fell in love with baseball. Growing up in Japan\, she recalls her 
 experience with the sport was not particularly gendered. It was not until 
 she attempted to attend a baseball camp in the US\, and was told it was on
 ly for boys\, that she realized she may face some obstacles to achieving h
 er diamond dreams. Like many Swarthmore students\, Laura approached these 
 obstacles as a challenge rather than a deterrent\, and at 26 years old has
  become a global face of women's baseball. Her resume includes being the f
 irst\, and thus far only\, woman to represent Great Britain in U18 basebal
 l\; becoming the first "ball girl" for the New York Yankees during the fir
 st Major League Baseball game played in England in 2019\; and being drafte
 d in the fifth round in the inaugural draft of the US-based Women's Profes
 sional Baseball League\, which is set to begin play in August. Laura also 
 played varsity softball at Swarthmore. Laura Hirai ’22 graduated with a 
 Bachelor of Arts in Arabic and Spanish. A dual-sport athlete at the intern
 ational level\, she is also the first person to represent Great Britain in
  both baseball and softball simultaneously at the national level\, pitchin
 g at the European Baseball Championships in 2015 and 2017. One of only thr
 ee European athletes selected in the inaugural Women's Professional Baseba
 ll League draft\, Laura most recently helped Great Britain claim gold in w
 omen's baseball and bronze in softball at the European Championships\, wit
 h both teams earning World Cup berths. SwatTalks is an Alumni Council init
 iative that engages the broader Swarthmore community through webinars feat
 uring alumni and faculty members excelling in their fields. Each hour-long
  online seminar is free and open to Swarthmore alumni\, families\, faculty
 \, staff\, students\, and friends. We welcome suggestions for future speak
 ers and topics — please email your ideas to alumni@swarthmore.edu.  \\n
 Details: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26ev
 entid%3D1380668585
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1380668585
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
