DTSTAMP:20260508T121334Z
DTSTART:20260516T200000Z
DTEND:20260516T210000Z
SUMMARY:2026 CCC Spring Concert
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Chester Children's Chorus"]\\nCategory: Perform
 ance\\nJoin our 110 Chester children for their spring concerts featuring c
 lassical and choral works\, followed by The Beatles' greatest hits\, inclu
 ding "Hey Jude\," "Help!\," Lucy in the Sky With Diamonds\," "Let It Be\,"
  and more. These will be the final performances of CCC Founder\, Executive
  & Artistic Director John Alston\, before his retirement in August 2026. "
 Who doesn't want to finish a musical career with The Beatles? They gave us
  some of the world's most compelling melodies\," said Alston. "I can barel
 y contain myself when our children sing the 'Hey Jude' hook." Guests are i
 nvited to post-concert receptions in the Lang Performing Arts Center (LPAC
 )\, which is adjacent to the Lang Concert Hall. Please note: due to extrao
 rdinary interest in John Alston’s final concerts before his retirement\,
  we’ve added a third show. We ask guests to attend one performance\, so
  more people can share in this special moment. Overflow seating will be av
 ailable next door in the Lang Performing Arts Center (LPAC)\, where guests
  can watch the performance livestream.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swar
 thmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1395460124
LOCATION:Lang Performing Arts Center Lobby (LPAC)\, Lang Music Building Roo
 m 214-Presser Room\, Lang Music Concert Hall\, Lang Music Building Upper L
 obby\, Lang Music Building Lower Lobby
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1395460124
CATEGORIES:Performance
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6fb211aeaef65783@swarthmore-dash-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260508T121334Z
DTSTART:20260516T233000Z
DTEND:20260517T003000Z
SUMMARY:The Garnet Choir is touring the United Kingdom this May
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['College Advancement']\\nCategory: Performance\\
 nThe Garnet Choir is touring the United Kingdom this May. We invite our UK
  alumni to attend any of the following performances to hear the ensemble
 ’s current repertoire. The students would love to see you in the audienc
 e as they share their work with international listeners. Performance Sched
 ule: Saturday\, May 16 | 7:30 p.m. Performing with the Reading Bach Choir 
 at St. James's Church\, Sussex Gardens\, London (W2 3UD). Purchase tickets
  here for £15.00. A meet-and-greet will follow the performance\, with cho
 ir members and alumni continuing the evening at The Swan for those who wou
 ld like to join. Tuesday\, May 19 | 5:30 p.m. Evensong with Selwyn College
  Choir at Selwyn College Chapel\, Cambridge Wednesday\, May 20 | 5:30 p.m.
  Evensong at Ely Cathedral\, Ely Thursday\, May 21 | 1:00 p.m. Lunchtime C
 oncert at Ely Cathedral\, Ely There is no formal registration or fee requi
 red for these events\, except for the St. James's Church performance — s
 imply arrive and enjoy the music. Guests are more than welcome to attend\,
  so please feel free to bring family and friends along. We hope you can at
 tend and enjoy a performance during the Garnet Choir’s UK tour! Warmly\,
 Swarthmore College Alumni\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?t
 rumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1395463328
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1395463328
CATEGORIES:Performance
END:VEVENT
